Iavan Pijoos, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bloemfontein - A Nigerian man, known as the "vampire", has been denied bail in the Bloemfontein Magistrate&rsquo;s Court, police said on Wednesday.Emmanuel Okiri, 38, appeared in court on Monday following his arrest in downtown Bloemfontein on Saturday evening around 21:00.Okiri allegedly bites his victims' ears, noses and mouths during his attacks, leaving them with huge scars, Constable Maselela Langa said.&nbsp;Langa said Okiri was wanted on four counts of assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm.The cases were opened in January, July, October and November.&nbsp;Okiri was expected to appear in court on Monday, November 28, for his formal bail application.&nbsp;He was arrested during the Lungisa intelligence operation where a tavern was closed and second hand goods for non-compliance were confiscated.&nbsp;The tavern owner was also arrested for possession of suspected stolen property.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.